    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of April 25 headline about drop in sales of existing homes; historical context explained</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A headline in Business Day on Wednesday about the drop in sales of existing homes in March to 6.12 million units, on a seasonally adjusted annual basis, misstated the historical context of those sales. While the drop of 8.4 percent was indeed the steepest monthly decline since January 1989, when sales fell by 12.6 percent; the sales did not fall to the 1989 level. (The sales rate for 1989 was 3.29 million units.)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
